<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10146539>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Parapenaeopsis tenella (Bate, 1888), a, c, female cl 13.5 mm (NTOU M02393); b, male cl 9.5 mm (NTOU M02393). a, carapace and anterior appendages, lateral view. b, petasma, ventral view. c, thelycum, ventral view. Scales: a, 5 mm; b, 1 mm; c, 3 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10146539/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10146541>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Parapeneopsis venusta De Man, 1907, a, c, female cl 15.7 mm (NTOU M02395); b, male cl 13.6 mm (NTOU M02394). a, carapace and anterior appendages, lateral view. b, petasma, ventral view. c, thelycum, ventral view. Scales: a, 5 mm; b, 1 mm; c, 3 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10146541/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10146543>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. a, Parapenaeopsis amicus V.C. Nguyên, 1971, female cl 29.5 mm (NTOU M02417). b, P. cornuta (Kishinouye, 1900), male cl 14.5 mm (NTOU M02357). c, P. hardwickii (Miers, 1878), female cl 30.3 mm (NTOU M02610). d, P. hardwickii (Miers, 1878), male (from Chan & Yu 1986, specimen lost). e, P. tenella (Bate, 1888), female cl 16.7 mm (NTOU M02392). f, P. venusta De Man, 1907, females cl 17.3 mm (NTOU M02395)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10146543/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

